name: r-fsa
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.9.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-fsa
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/FSA_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/FSA/FSA_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3c102c2bab42ae3ffbf1180eaca4d48814f11fd0af3f684ef2f68593430a5d81

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-car
    - r-dplyr
    - r-dunn.test
    - r-lmtest
    - r-plotrix
    - r-sciplot
    - r-withr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-car
    - r-dplyr
    - r-dunn.test
    - r-lmtest
    - r-plotrix
    - r-sciplot
    - r-withr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('FSA')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('FSA')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/droglenc/FSA
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: A variety of simple fish stock assessment methods. Detailed vignettes are available on the fishR website <http://derekogle.com/fishR/>.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - droglenc
